==English==

===Etymology===
Perhaps from the WWI era, from the British practice of using ''Chinese'' as a slur; now used only as a festive exclamation.

{{Wikipedia}}

===Noun phrase===
'''Chinese fire drill'''
# A [[prank]] performed while stopped in a car at a red-light; all pasengers (including the driver) shout "CHINESE FIRE DRILL," exit the vehicle, run at least once around the vehicle then return to a different seat.
# A silly, pointless exercise.

{{-usage-}}
Although this term has seemed to have lost all traces of an insulting meaning, it is possible some might be offended.